Electrum-Vert - lightweight Vertcoin client

Licence: GNU GPL v3
Electrum Author: Thomas Voegtlin
Electrum-Vert Contributors: Riccardo Spagni, Michael Wozniak
Language: Python
Electrum Homepage: http://electrum.org/

Electrum-Vert Homepage: http://electrum-vert.org/


1. GETTING STARTED
------------------

To run Electrum-Vert from this directory, just do:

  ./electrum-vert

If you install Electrum on your system, you can run it from any
directory:

  sudo python setup.py install

To start Electrum-Vert from your web browser, see
http://electrum-vert.org/bitcoin_URIs.html



2. HOW OFFICIAL PACKAGES ARE CREATED
------------------------------------

python mki18n.py
pyrcc4 icons.qrc -o gui/qt/icons_rc.py
python setup.py sdist --format=zip,gztar

On Mac OS X:

  # On port based installs
  sudo python setup-release.py py2app

  # On brew installs
  ARCHFLAGS="-arch i386 -arch x86_64" sudo python setup-release.py py2app --includes sip

  sudo hdiutil create -fs HFS+ -volname "Electrum-Vert" -srcfolder dist/Electrum-Vert.app dist/electrum-vert-VERSION-macosx.dmg

